Let my offer a solution to your actual problem.

&gt; I tried:
&gt; - Setting Position to poOwnerFormCenter, worked but always ended up on the primary monitor.

Well, `poOwnerFormCenter` should work. But you must specify the owner.

For instance,

    procedure TForm1.Button1Click(Sender: TObject);
    var
      dlg: TMyDialog;
    begin
      dlg := TMyDialog.Create(Self);
      try
        dlg.ShowModal;
      finally
        dlg.Free;
      end;
    end;

The owner is passed as the argument of the constructor, in this case `Self`. This is the &quot;owner&quot; referred to in &quot;owner form center&quot;.

